      <hedline>
        <hl1>Speed Demon</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Women's Sports &amp; Fitness editor in chief Lucy S Danziger letter on Thomas Hackett's May 14 profile of track star Marion Jones holds confidence is Jones' key to success</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Thomas Hackett traveled to North Carolina in the hope of understanding ''the reasons for Marion Jones's magnificence.'' He then proceeded to take Jones down for her supreme confidence. He characterized as unsympathetic her belief that she can win an unprecedented five Olympic gold medals in track and field.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Thomas Hackett traveled to North Carolina in the hope of understanding ''the reasons for Marion Jones's magnificence.'' He then proceeded to take Jones down for her supreme confidence. He characterized as unsympathetic her belief that she can win an unprecedented five Olympic gold medals in track and field.</p>
        <p>It is exactly such confidence that is the key to Jones's success. Other than choosing your parents well, the main difference between the athletic champion and the rest of us is mental toughness.</p>
        <p>Lucy S. Danziger  Editor in Chief  Women's Sports &amp; Fitness  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
